Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Mix chicken, soup, 1/2 cup of the sour cream, 1 cup of the cheese and 3 Tbsp. of the cilantro until well blended. Spoon about 1/4 cup of the chicken mixture down center of each tortilla; roll up. Place, seam sides down, in greased 13x9-inch baking dish. Top with the salsa and remaining cheese. Bake 25 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining 1 Tbsp. cilantro; top with the remaining 1/2 cup sour cream.